	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Sun Apr 05, 2009 8:22 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And there's no way to simulate those with audio? I'm just curious, I know nothing about audio and video signals.</div>
<br />
<br />Sure you could. You just need a ~60/50Hz pulse wave and a ~15723/15625Hz pulse wave. Only problem is that the NES has a maximum pulse wave frequency of 14kHz, which most TVs won't sync to. Depending on the television, you might be able to drive at the first undertone (~8kHz) and have it sync.
<br />
<br />Drawing things in addition to generating sync will be nontrivial, however.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


